org.wattdepot.client.http.api

Class WattDepotClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.wattdepot.client.http.api.WattDepotClient
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    WattDepotInterface
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    WattDepotAdminClient

    public class WattDepotClient
extends Object
implements WattDepotInterface
    WattDepotClient - high-level Java implementation that communicates with a WattDepot server. It implements the WattDepotInterface that hides the HTTP Labels.
    Author:
    Cam Moore

    • Constructor Detail

      • WattDepotClient

        public WattDepotClient(String serverUri,
               String username,
               String orgId,
               String password)
                throws BadCredentialException
        Creates a new WattDepotClient.
        Parameters:
        serverUri - The URI of the WattDepot server (e.g. "http://server.wattdepot.org/")
        username - The name of the user. The user must be defined in the WattDepot server.
        orgId - the organization the user is in.
        password - The password for the user.
        Throws:
        BadCredentialException - If the user or password don't match the credentials on the WattDepot server.

      • getDescriptiveStats

        public DescriptiveStats getDescriptiveStats(Depository depository,
                                   Sensor sensor,
                                   Date timestamp,
                                   Boolean daily,
                                   Integer samples,
                                   Boolean pointValues)
        Specified by:
        getDescriptiveStats in interface WattDepotInterface
        Parameters:
        depository - The Depository storing the Measurements.
        sensor - The Sensor making the Measurements.
        timestamp - The time to base the historical values calculation on.
        daily - if true, use daily grouping of values, if false use hourly grouping.
        samples - How many samples to use to calculate the values. Corresponds to weeks.
        pointValues - if true use point value, use difference values otherwise.
        Returns:
        The DescriptiveStats for the given sensor and depository using samples.
